Task: 07
Title: Application ensemble services
Phase: 2
Route: full
Slice: Panel Fan-out + Synthesis, Judge Analysis
Dependencies: 06
Scope: Implement the three application services that form the ensemble pipeline: PanelRunner (dispatches parallel ChatModelPort.complete() calls via Promise.allSettled, collects failed_models, throws FusionError('all_panels_failed') when every model rejects), JudgeStep (calls ChatModelPort.complete() with responseFormat json_object, parses via safeParseAnalysis, returns Analysis | null on failure without throwing, logs errors via LoggerPort), and SynthesizeStep (calls ChatModelPort.complete() with synthesis prompt, accepts optional Analysis parameter). All services depend only on ChatModelPort and domain types — zero infrastructure imports.
Acceptance Criteria: AC-7 (partial — PanelRunner logic), AC-8 (partial — JudgeStep logic), AC-9 (partial — SynthesizeStep)
NFRs: NFR-1, NFR-5
Gate Criteria: Phase 2 Gate 1 (services ready for orchestration), Phase 2 Gate 2 (JudgeStep returns null on failure)
Files:
  - src/application/usecases/panel-runner.ts (CREATE) — PanelRunner: run(request, panelModels) → { responses: PanelResponse[]; failedModels: FailedModelInfo[] }; throws FusionError('all_panels_failed') on total failure
  - src/application/usecases/judge-step.ts (CREATE) — JudgeStep: analyze(panelResponses) → Promise<Analysis | null>; uses ChatModelPort.complete() with responseFormat json_object, safeParseAnalysis, logs errors without throwing
  - src/application/usecases/synthesize-step.ts (CREATE) — SynthesizeStep: synthesize(request, panelResponses, analysis?) → Promise<string>; builds prompt from panel outputs and optional analysis, calls ChatModelPort.complete() (non-streamed)
